I took hgipperich's advice and only used a tbsp of (raw) sugar. The result was fantastic and my wife loved the dish.

Rating: 3
I used 1 tbsp of sugar instead of the ¼ cup listed. Great flavor! I served it with rice pilaf and grilled asparagus. My dinner guest practically licked her plate clean.

Rating: 4
I don't ever know what to do with beef - and this recipe helped me get it right. I was surprised by how tender the meat was - how flavorful. Usually red meat is so rich I can only eat a bite or two and then I'm overpowered, but this was light and tasty even though it was rich. I ate my whole serving! Also - nice that it was low fat!

